OSX Sees Brazil Market for Rigs, Platforms at $200 Billion

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-04-14T16:10:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/osx-sees-brazil-market-for-rigs-platforms-at-200-billion.html
OSX Brasil SA (OSXB3) , the oil-services
company controlled by billionaire  Eike Batista , is ramping up
its ship-building operations amid expectations the Brazilian
market for rigs and platforms will total $200 billion over the
next 10 years, the finance chief said.  OSX plans to start building a shipyard at the Acu port in
May after getting an “installation license” from Rio de Janeiro
state’s environmental agency in the next few weeks, Chief
Financial Officer Roberto Monteiro said today in a telephone
interview in Rio de Janeiro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Millard in Rio de Janeiro at 
 pmillard1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jessica Brice at 
 jbrice1@bloomberg.net  